A '''disruptor field''', also '''field disruptor''', was a type of field projection that interfered with electronic systems and coherent energy fields. The [[Rakata/Legends|Rakatan]] [[Infinite Empire/Legends|Infinite Empire]] was known to devastate planets with disruptor fields.

In [[3956 BBY]], a disruptor field projected from the [[Temple of the Ancients]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Lehon/Legends|Lehon]] forced down [[Revan/Legends|Revan's]] ship, the ''[[Ebon Hawk]]'', by creating electrical overloads and disruptions. In order to reach the [[Star Forge]], Revan and his companions disabled the disruptor field by manipulating the controls located on the Temple Summit. The Sith fleet in orbit had shielding against this type of technology, and were not affected by the field.<ref name="KotOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref>

On some of the worlds of the [[Rakatan Archipelago]], a collection of holdouts in the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] that survived the fall of the Infinite Empire, certain tribes of Rakata regained access to their worlds' disruptor fields, using them to disable and plunder incoming vessels.<ref name="TUR">''[[The Unknown Regions]]''</ref>

During the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], a field disruptor could be small and mobile, which caused soldiers on the [[Deflector shield/Legends|shielded]] world of [[Gyndine/Legends|Gyndine]] to inspect incoming [[refugee]]s for field disruptors.

